      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You must never adjust your warfarin dosage without consulting your prescribing physician. Warfarin is a powerful medication, and even a small change can drastically affect your blood clotting time. Your doctor needs to monitor your INR levels regularly to ensure the dose remains perfectly balanced for your specific heart condition. Please schedule an appointment to discuss your current symptoms and lab results with them before making any changes.",
      "source": "target",
